      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent GCI analysis on at least three systematically refined meshes; discretization error reported as explicit uncertainty bound on QoI.",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence index (GCI) analysis performed on three mesh levels (4.2M, 11.8M, 28.5M cells). GCI for nIH at the nominal operating point is 9.3%, which exceeds the MRL 5 target of ≤5%. Near-wall resolution in the volute tongue region was identified as the primary contributor to residual discretization error."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions documented with uncertainty; inlet velocity profiles, fluid temperature, and hematocrit measured and reported.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark PIV dataset provides well-characterized boundary conditions. Hemolysis bench tests documented inlet flow rate (±1.5%), rotational speed (±0.3%), and temperature (±0.5°C). Hematocrit variation across donors (35–45%) introduces unquantified biological variability not fully captured in the CFD inlet conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison with experimental uncertainty bands; statistical metric (e.g., U95) reported for each QoI at each operating condition.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed for nIH at 5 operating points. U95 experimental uncertainty estimated at ±12% for hemolysis measurements. CFD predictions fall within U95 at 4 of 5 conditions; the high-speed low-flow outlier (23% deviation) exceeds the uncertainty band. Formal validation metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 E-factor) not computed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation are identical to or directly translatable to the clinical decision QoIs without additional assumptions.",
      "rationale": "Validation QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (nIH) from bench experiments using bovine blood. Clinical decision QoI is absolute plasma-free hemoglobin rise rate in human patients. Translation from nIH to clinical hemolysis requires species correction and in-vivo hemodynamic scaling factors that introduce model-form uncertainty not quantified in this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, flow regime, and operating envelope match COU device geometry and intended operating range; any extrapolation documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is a simplified research analog. COU device is a proprietary axial-centrifugal hybrid design with a different impeller topology. Geometric similarity is limited; Reynolds number ranges overlap but blade loading distributions differ substantially. Extrapolation from validation geometry to COU device is not formally bounded."
    },
