      "rationale": "No independent use-error review has been performed. Simulation setup and post-processing were conducted by the same analyst team. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty quantified via alternative model comparison or Bayesian model averaging; dominant model-form assumptions justified for COU flow regime.",
      "rationale": "Power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) used as the primary constitutive relation. Alternative model (Bludszuweit) evaluated at two operating points showing 15–30% divergence in predicted nIH. No Bayesian model averaging or formal model-form uncertainty quantification performed. Turbulence model sensitivity (k-ω SST vs. SST-CC) not evaluated."
    },
